    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "executeQuery",
        "query": "SELECT \"YEAR\", \"MONTH\" FROM FLIGHTS.FLIGHTS GROUP BY \"YEAR\", \"MONTH\" ORDER BY \"YEAR\" DESC, \"MONTH\" DESC LIMIT 1",
        "restrictToSelect": true,
        "executionMode": "sequentially"
      },
      "id": "d1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
      "name": "Find Latest Month",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-exasol.exasol",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        300,
        0
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "exasolApi": {
          "id": "ExasolDemoDbCred",
          "name": "Exasol Demo DB"
        }
      },
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "maxTries": 3,
      "waitBetweenTries": 1000
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "executeQuery",
        "query": "SELECT OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER AS CARRIER, COUNT(*) AS FLIGHT_COUNT, ROUND(AVG(ARR_DELAY), 1) AS AVG_ARR_DELAY_MIN FROM FLIGHTS.FLIGHTS WHERE \"YEAR\" = ? AND \"MONTH\" = ? GROUP BY OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER ORDER BY FLIGHT_COUNT DESC LIMIT 10",
        "restrictToSelect": true,
        "parameters": {
          "values": [
            {
              "value": "={{ $json.YEAR }}"
            },
            {
              "value": "={{ $json.MONTH }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "executionMode": "sequentially"
      },
      "id": "d1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003",
      "name": "Top Carriers",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-exasol.exasol",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        600,
        0
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "exasolApi": {
          "id": "ExasolDemoDbCred",
          "name": "Exasol Demo DB"
        }
      },
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "maxTries": 3,
      "waitBetweenTries": 1000
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Demo 1 — Flight Delay Report\n\nFinds the most recent month of data in `FLIGHTS.FLIGHTS` (~185M rows) and reports the **top-10 carriers** of that month by flight count, with their average arrival delay.\n\n**Read-only** — both queries keep *Restrict to SELECT Queries* enabled and aggregate with `GROUP BY` + `LIMIT`.\n\n**Expected output:** 10 items with `CARRIER`, `FLIGHT_COUNT`, `AVG_ARR_DELAY_MIN`.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 860,
        "color": 5
      },
